# Enum System (CORE_ENUM + EnumUtils)

## Critical Rule

❌ **NEVER** write: `enum class MyEnum { Value1, Value2 };`  
✅ **ALWAYS** write: `CORE_ENUM(MyEnum, uint8_t, Value1, Value2);`

## Usage

Use `CORE_ENUM(Name, UnderlyingType, Values...)` in any namespace. Access utilities via `EnumUtils<Enum>`:

- `EnumUtils<MyEnum>::ToString(e)` - enum to string
- `EnumUtils<MyEnum>::FromString(str)` - string to enum
- `EnumUtils<MyEnum>::Cast(str)` - safe parsing (returns `std::optional`)
- `EnumUtils<MyEnum>::ToPoolString(e)` - enum to PoolString
